column1: Changed so that instead of saving the exact response time for each request , the response time is rounded ( 67 - > 67 , 124 - > 120 , 1470 - > 1500 and 58459 - > 58000 ) . This is done so that the response times can be sent to the master node - without taking up an enormous amount of bandwidth - when running in distributed mode , instead of just sending the median ( which results in incorrect response time distribution stats ) .
